      <h2>Prolific Inventor</h2>
      <p>Prolific Inventor Dr. Lavian has invented over 120 patents, 60 of which he has prosecuted pro-se before the US Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO). In this area of work, he focuses on network communicators, computer networks, Internet Protocols (TCP/IP), VoIP, streaming media, and Web technologies. Dr. Lavian has extensive work experience in network communications, including eleven years with Silicon Valley-based, Nortel Networks, a global telecommunications and networking equipment leader, where he has held several positions, including principal scientist, architect, and senior software engineer. While working for Nortel Networks, Dr. Lavian created and chaired the company's EDN Patent Committee. He enabled Nortel Networks to secure its intellectual property (IP) rights. He also helped the company generate a continuous stream of innovative ideas for switches, routers, and network communications devices, allowing the company to significantly enrich its IP portfolio, a portion of which was later sold for $4.5 billion.</p>

      <h2>Inventions and Patents in the following technologies:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>TCP/IP suite, TCP, UDP, and IP</li>
        <li>Ethernet, MAC, PHY, and the 802.3 standards</li>
        <li>LANs, WANs, VPNs, QoS, switching, packet switching</li>
        <li>VoIP, SIP, RTP, IP telephony, multimedia, video/audio streaming, audio/video conferencing, streaming media</li>
        <li>SMS, MMS, instant messaging (IM), text messaging, short messages, chat apps via video and audio</li>
        <li>Network protocols and software applications, content switching, and load balancing</li>
        <li>Routing protocols&mdash;from RIP, BGP, MPLS, and OSPF to multicast, PSTN, and SS7</li>
        <li>Wireless LAN (WLAN), mobile wireless, Wi-Fi, and the 802.11 standards</li>
        <li>Network security, firewalls, VPNs, IPSec, Tunneling, SSL, HTTPS, Security Gateways, IDS, and IPS</li>
      </ul>

